  # 72 Mencione una guerra durante los años 1800 en la que peleo los Estados Unidos.
    ["Name one war fought by the United States in the 1800s.\n1) Civil War\n2) Vietnam War\n3) World War II", "1", "1 - The United States fought four major wars in the 1800s-the War of 1812, the Mexican-American War, the Civil War, and the Spanish-American War.", "rev. 02/16", "Spanish"],
    
    ["Name one war fought by the US in the 1800s.\n1) Civil War\n2) Spanish-American War\n3) World War I\n4) Vietnam War\n5) 1 & 3\n6) 3 & 4\n7) 1 & 2\n8) 2 & 3", "7", "7 - The United States fought four major wars in the 1800s-the War of 1812, the Mexican-American War, the Civil War, and the Spanish-American War.", "rev. 02/16", "Spanish"],
  # 73 De el nombre de la guerra entre el Norte y el Sur de los Estados Unidos.
    ["The American Civil War is also known as the War between the States.\n1) Verdadero\n2) Falso", "1", "1 - It was a war between the people in the northern states and those in the southern states, but most battles were fought in the southern states.", "rev. 02/16", "Spanish"],

    ["Name the U.S. war between the North and the South.\n1) the War of 1812\n2) the Mexican-American War\n3) the Spanish-American War\n4) the Civil War", "4", "4 - The American Civil War is also known as the War between the States. It was a war between the people in the northern states and those in the southern states.", "rev. 02/16", "Spanish"],
  # 74 Mencione un problema que condujo a la Guerra Civil.
    ["Name one problem that led to the Civil War.\n1) slavery\n2) economic reasons\n3) states' rights\n4) 1 & 2\n5) 1 & 3\n6) all of the above\n7) none of the above", "6", "6 - slavery, economic reasons and states' rights are all problems that led to the Civil War.", "rev. 02/16", "Spanish"],

    ["The Civil War began when 11 southern states voted to secede from the US to form their own country, the Confederate States of America.\n1) Verdadero\n2) Falso", "1", "1 - These southern states believed that the federal government of the United States threatened their right to make their own decisions.", "rev. 02/16", "Spanish"],

    ["Economic reasons led to the Civil War.\n1) Verdadero\n2) Falso", "1", "1 - slavery, economic reasons and states' rights are all problems that led to the Civil War.", "rev. 02/16", "Spanish"],
    
    ["Slavery did not lead to the Civil War.\n1) Verdadero\n2) Falso", "2", "2 - slavery, economic reasons and states' rights are all problems that led to the Civil War.", "rev. 02/16", "Spanish"],
    
    ["States' rights led to the Civil War.\n1) Verdadero\n2) Falso", "1", "1 - slavery, economic reasons and states' rights are all problems that led to the Civil War.", "rev. 02/16", "Spanish"],
  # 75 ¿Que fue una cosa importante que hizo Abraham Lincoln?
    ["What was one important thing that Abraham Lincoln did?\n1) stood against the Emancipation Proclamation\n2) saved the Confederate army\n3) freed the slaves", "3", "3 - During the Civil War, he issued the Emancipation Proclamation. It declared that the slaves who lived in the rebelling Confederate states were forever free.", "rev. 02/16", "Spanish"],

    ["What was one important thing that Abraham Lincoln did?\n1) became vice president\n2) saved (or preserved) the Union\n3) led the separation of states", "2", "2 - Lincoln thought the separation of southern (Confederate) states was unconstitutional. He wanted to preserve the Union & issued the Emancipation Proclamation.", "rev. 02/16", "Spanish"],

    ["What was one important thing that Abraham Lincoln did?\n1) Emancipation Proclamation\n2) preserved the Union\n3) led the US during the Civil War\n4) 1, 2 & 3", "4", "4 - Abraham Lincoln was president of the US from 1861 to 1865, led the nation during the Civil War, preserved the Union and issued the Emancipation Proclamation", "rev. 02/16", "Spanish"],
  # 76 ¿Que hizo la Proclamacion de la Emancipacion?
    ["What did the Emancipation Proclamation do? It freed slaves in the:\n1) Confederate (southern) states\n2) Union (northern) states\n3) western states\n4) no state", "1", "1 - The Emancipation Proclamation declared that slaves living in the southern or Confederate states were free. Many slaves joined the Union army.", "rev. 02/16", "Spanish"],

    ["Freed slaves in the Confederacy were a result of the Emancipation Proclamation.\n1) Verdadero\n2) Falso", "1", "1 - The Emancipation Proclamation declared that slaves living in the southern or Confederate states were free. Many slaves joined the Union army.", "rev. 02/16", "Spanish"],

    ["The Emancipation Proclamation led to the 2nd Amendment to the Constitution, which ended slavery in all of the United States.\n1) Verdadero\n2) Falso", "2", "2 - In 1865, the Civil War ended and the southern slaves kept their right to be free, which led the 13th Amendment to the Constitution.", "rev. 02/16", "Spanish"],
  # 77 ¿Que hizo Susan B. Anthony?
